In a speech at United Performance Metals in Hamilton, Ohio, President Biden emphasized the importance of manufacturing and innovation in the United States. He highlighted the need to bring back manufacturing jobs to the country and strengthen the resilience of supply chains. The President discussed the potential of 3D printing technology to reduce costs and improve productivity in manufacturing. He also stressed the importance of investing in research and development to stay competitive with other countries, particularly China. The President urged Congress to pass the Bipartisan Innovation Act, which would make significant investments in American innovation and manufacturing. He expressed his optimism about America's future and its ability to lead in the 21st century.